Odaily Planet Daily News According to official news, Solayer announced the launch of the infiniSVM development network (devnet), which is a general execution layer that supports hardware acceleration and unlimited expansion. It has now opened basic services including RPC interfaces, API interfaces, faucets and block browsers for developers to deploy contracts, simulate production loads, test edge scenarios and feedback problems.
The core features of infiniSVM include:
Multi-execution architecture: each application runs on an independent execution unit;
Unlimited scalability: the execution units are connected via Infiniband high-speed communication;
Hardware offloading: using dedicated computing and storage clusters with RDMA capabilities;
Parallel processing mechanism: supports speculative preprocessing of transactions and improves execution throughput;
Bridge architecture optimization: sharing Solana and infiniSVM program code, without switching chain IDs, to achieve instant confirmation of cross-chain calls.
Solayer also launched a native development network token exchange function to enhance the development experience.
